# Modularity & Architecture Enforcement

## File Size Governance

| Threshold | Lines | Action |
|-----------|-------|--------|
| Preferred | < 400 | OK |
| Soft warn | 500 | Note it in response |
| Refactor | 700 | Propose a split |
| Mandatory | 900 | Must split before adding more code |
| Absolute | 1200 | Refuse to add code; split first |

When a file exceeds 700 lines, list its responsibilities and propose specific modules.

## Function Limits

- Preferred: < 40 lines
- Warning: > 60 lines
- Must refactor: > 100 lines
- Max nesting depth: 3
- Max branches per function: 8

## Dependency Limits

- Max imports per file: 10 (preferred < 6)
- If exceeded, introduce a service layer or utilities module

## Single Responsibility Principle

Before adding code, ask: "Does this belong in this module?"
If not, create a new module. Never grow a module just because it already exists.

## Store Design (Pinia/Vue)

1 store = 1 system. Stores handle state + orchestration only.

Stores must NOT contain: heavy algorithms, large utilities, networking logic, or file system logic. Move those into `services/`.

## Project Structure

```
stores/       State + orchestration
services/     Business logic, API calls, networking
utils/        Pure functions, algorithms, math
components/   UI components
composables/  Reusable Vue composition logic
```

## Algorithm Isolation

Extract complex logic into dedicated utility files (e.g. `booleanOps.js`, `geometryUtils.js`, `zIndexUtils.js`). Stores orchestrate; they do not compute.

## Naming

Name modules by domain, not generic terms.

Good: `moodBoardItemsStore`, `canvasViewportService`, `boardExportService`
Bad: `helpers.js`, `utils2.js`, `miscFunctions.js`, `store2.js`

## Self-Check Before Finishing

Before completing a response, evaluate:
- Is this modular?
- Does this create long-term technical debt?
- Would this scale to a 100k-line codebase?

If any answer is no, redesign before delivering.
